ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said it was understood that the man had been working on the roof when he had apparently lost his footing.Paramedics arrived on the scene to find the man s wife standing next to him. Paramedics assessed the man and found that he had sustained a serious injury to his head and neck leaving him in a critical condition. Paramedics immediately began their treatment and provided the man with advanced life support interventions. Once treated the man was transported to a private hospital for urgent treatment Meiring said.